# Experiment B (H2 probe) — H1 fire-under-lock RESTORED (stock); only the
# victim-side waits at tryCacheGetBy and tryCachePutBy locker entry made
# stop-aware (tryLock loop with GCClient heap access released).
# Applied 2026-06-10; binary snapshot kept at
# WebKitBuild/Release/bin/jsc-bughunt-expB.
# Result: repro4 x30 = 22 pass / 4 WATCHDOG-ABORT / 4 TIMEOUT(150s hang).
# Abort core bts/expB-core-807636.bt: victim wedged at a THIRD, unpatched
# blind locker on the same codeBlock->m_lock — fireWatchpointsAndClearStubIfNeeded
# (Repatch.cpp:518, via tryCacheGetBy:963) — while the restored 1360 fire held
# the lock as conductor (deferred=0x0). H2 sufficiency (two-site closure)
# REFUTED; victim-side gap is a CLASS of Section-7 lock waits. The 4 silent
# 150s hangs (no watchdog => world stop completed or none pending) are a new
# shape introduced by the probe itself — consistent with the probe's
# acquireHeapAccess-while-holding-m_lock tail interacting with in-window work
# that takes m_lock; not pinned (SIGKILL, no core).
#
# NOTE: hand-written patch (git unavailable in this run).

--- a/Source/JavaScriptCore/runtime/ConcurrentJSLock.h
@@ ConcurrentJSLockerBase @@
+    // BUGHUNT H2 probe (NOT FOR LANDING): adopt an already-held lock.
+    explicit ConcurrentJSLockerBase(WTF::AdoptLockTag, ConcurrentJSLock& lockable) WTF_IGNORES_THREAD_SAFETY_ANALYSIS
+    {
